        @{"BUTTON_SelAnimImages" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/button.h/File" 97} (@{"struct Image" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/intuition.h/File" 705} *)  (V42)
            Sets an array of alternate images for a selected state
            if used, must contain an equal number of images as the
            array used for @{"BUTTON_AnimImages" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/button.h/File" 94}.  It's wise to use the
            same sized images too

            Defaults to @{"NULL" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 101}.

            Applicability is (@{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63}, @{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65})

        @{"BUTTON_MaxAnimImages" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/button.h/File" 104} (@{"LONG" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 51})  (V42)
            Number of images available in the arrays

            Defaults to 0.

            Applicability is (@{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63}, @{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65})

        @{"BUTTON_AnimImageNumber" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/button.h/File" 107} (@{"LONG" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 51})  (V42)
            Current image number in the array(s) to use the range of
            available frames is 0 .. MaxAnimImages-1

            Defaults to 0.

            Applicability is (@{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63}, @{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65})

        @{"BUTTON_AddAnimImageNumber" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/button.h/File" 112} (@{"ULONG" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 52})  (V42)
           Value to be added to the current image number counter
           the counter will wrap around at MaxAnimImages

            Applicability is (@{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65}, @{"OM_UPDATE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 70})

        @{"BUTTON_SubAnimImageNumber" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/button.h/File" 117} (@{"ULONG" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 52})  (V42)
            Value to be subtracted from the current image number counter
            the counter will wrap around when less than 0

            Applicability is (@{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65}, @{"OM_UPDATE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 70})

    BUGS
        Unfortunetly, this class shares the same filename and tag range
        as the button gadget released by David Junod of C=, released in
        the GI1.lha V42 beta archive on BIX, and later the AT DevCD.
        We admit it, we screwed up... but its not a majorly serious issue
        as this class is atleast 90% compatible.

        A few rarely, possibly never, used tags of the original are @{"NOT" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/intuition.h/File" 1500}
        currently supported. The usage of @{"BUTTON_PushButton" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/button.h/File" 36} in ReAction is
        not totally compatible to Junod's. Ours acts like @{"GA_ToggleSelect" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/gadgetclass.h/File" 138}
        of Junod's.

        Please report any incompatibilities immediatly.

@ENDNODE
@NODE "BUTTON_GetClass" "button_gc/BUTTON_GetClass()"
@{b}

    NAME@{ub}
        @{"BUTTON_GetClass" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/button.h/File" 23} -- Gets the pointer to the button class.@{b}

    SYNOPSIS@{ub}
        button_class = @{"BUTTON_GetClass" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/button.h/File" 23}();
        D0

        Class * @{"BUTTON_GetClass" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/button.h/File" 23}(@{"VOID" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 24});@{b}

    FUNCTION@{ub}
        This function is only available in runtime linked version of the
        class, and is not in the compiler linker library button_gc.lib.

        Obtains the pointer to the Button gadget class for use with
        @{"NewObject()" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/intuition/NewObject"}.  This function always returns a valid pointer so
        you do not need to check it.  The reason is that if the library
        opens fine, then the pointer returned is already setup.  (Of course
        this implies that if opening the library fails, you shouldn't be
        calling this.)

        Note that this function does not create the class, that is done
        when the class library is opened.@{b}

    INPUTS@{ub}
        Nothing.@{b}

    RESULT@{ub}
        button_class - Pointer to the Button gadget class.@{b}

    SEE ALSO@{ub}

@ENDNODE
